I was in Brazil when Europe went into lockdown, hardly any of the foreigners took the pandemic seriously at first and we where all still enjoying life partying out in the streets. I eventually booked a flight for a few days later as my family urged me to do so and still thought I was overreacting. Little did I know that my flight was one of the last flights flying to the EU from Rio for a while. The people who decided to stay had to go to different airports and a lot of them weren’t even able to book online. All of their flights were incredibly expensive, almost 10 times what I had paid. Compared to what they went through my journey was relatively hassle free except for some confusion over a cancelled connection at Lisbon airport. Still made it home after 24 hours of traveling, 3 flights and 4 international airports. Arriving in Europe was dystopic and scary but I’m glad I didn’t choose to stay. Thinking I’ll stay home for the rest of 2020 and be very careful with travel plans for 2021. The reality of having to face potentially being stuck in a foreign country is scary and def not as fun as it may sound to some.
